{"word":"H2563 - חֹמֶר - chômer - kho'mer - Clay","slug":"H2563","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">חֹמֶר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>chômer"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kho'mer"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Clay"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D7;&#x05DE;&#x05E8; - cho&#x0302;mer</b> - <i>kho'-mer</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H2560\">H2560</a>; properly a <i>bubbling</i> up, that is, of water, a <i>wave</i>; of earth, <i>mire</i> or <i>clay</i> (cement); also a <i>heap</i>; hence a <i>chomer</i> or dry measure: - clay, heap, homer, mire, motion, mortar."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2565\">H2565</a>"}]}